text: Elena Ionescu (17 May 1988) is a Romanian singer who since 2006 has been the lead singer of pop band Mandinga replacing Elena Gheorghe. Mandinga won the Romanian national selection for the Eurovision Song Contest 2012 in Baku, Azerbaijan were Ionescu will sing the song Zaleilah. == References == Category:1988 births Category:Romanian singers Category:Living people
title: Elena Ionescu
